### How it works

| Step | What happens |
|------|-------------|
| **List** | `sempy_labs.list_lakehouses()` pulls every lakehouse in your workspace |
| **Locate tables** | Uses `dbutils.fs.ls()` on the OneLake ABFS path to find the Tables folder |
| **Schema detection** | Checks if the first folder contains parquet files (flat) or more folders (schema-based), and drills in accordingly |
| **Read test** | Does `spark.read.format("delta").load(...).limit(1).collect()` — the lightest possible read |
| **Access decision** | `Yes` if the read succeeds, `No` on any 403 / FileNotFound / exception |

